<TEXT>
fiftytwo students were arrested tuesday 
evening after occupying a university of massachusetts building 
overnight to protest defense departmentfunded research 
in new york city thousands of city college students got an 
unscheduled holiday after demonstrators occupied the campus 
administration building to protest possible tuition increases 
prompting officials to suspend classes 
about 60 police in riot gear arrived at the university of 
massachusetts around 5 pm about two hours later a bus drove away 
with 29 students who had camped inside memorial hall 
those students were charged with trespassing and another 23 
students were arrested for lying in front of the bus to prevent it 
from leaving police said 
about 300 students stood outside the building chanting and 
looking on as the students inside the hall were arrested 
about 35 students had occupied memorial hall since 1 pm 
monday they declined an offer to meet with administrators in the 
provosts office tuesday morning and instead presented a list of 
demands that included a halt to all defense department research at 
the 25000student campus 
about 40 students left the building tuesday morning after 
several university administrators told them they would be arrested 
after 5 pm said university spokeswoman jeanne hopkins 
the takeover was the second at the western massachusetts campus 
in a week seven protesters were arrested april 19 on charges of 
disorderly conduct and trespassing after also demonstrating against 
militaryfunded research on campus particularly research into 
anthrax 
all research at the university is nonclassified and researchers 
must make their work public under university rules about 116 
million or 22 percent of grant money received at the university 
came from the defense department in 1988 according to the school 
chancellor joseph d duffey issued a statement telling the 
students the research would continue on campus until school 
administrators decide differently 
the policy will not be negotiated with students duffey said 
the latest occupation began when students rallying monday at the 
student union against military research marched toward the 
administration building several then ducked into memorial hall en 
route and more followed 
members of the local chapter of the american friends service 
committee have contended that the research is dangerous to the 
town promotes militarism and should be banned 
the university has argued the purpose of the anthrax research is 
peaceful and the strain of bacteria used is nonvirulent and has 
been under study at the school for 23 years without incident 
the amherst health board has scheduled a hearing for wednesday 
on the question of the safety of the anthrax research 
tuesday was the first time since 1969 that classes at city 
college of new york have been canceled because of student protests 
said school spokesman charles deciccio 
protesters demanding a facetoface meeting with gov mario 
cuomo said they feared tuition at the college now 1250 a year 
would be increased and the college staff would be reduced because 
of state budget cuts 
the governor had no immediate comment 
tuition for next year has not been set deciccio said 
</TEXT>
