drivers and passengers in this carmad country will 
have to buckle up beginning thursday and keep the bambini in the 
back seat the government announced 
a communique from premier ciriaco de mitas office monday said 
that people caught without their seat belts on will be subject to 
fines ranging from 12000 lire 9 to 50000 lire 37 
the regulations do not apply to pregnant women the new rules 
also require babies and toddlers to be in car seats and relegate 
children up to the age of 12 to the back seat 
the regulations were drawn up by the ministries of the interior 
public works transport and health 
