suspected abortion mills in simultaneous raids partially clad 
women ran screaming from the premises as suspected abortionists 
were hauled into jail 
six people including barnett were charged with manslaughter of 
fetuses by abortion and maintaining a public nuisance as a result 
of the raids 
there were no figures on the number of women injured or killed 
by illegal abortions crick said 
there were some deaths but not wholesale deaths he said 
some women said they wished they hadnt had abortions 
others said hey look its nobodys business he said 
a lot of women were ending up unable to have children because 
of botched abortions it was protecting women against themselves 
he said of the raids 
he said he remembered that barnett ran a clean operation and her 
work was respected by the medical community barnett herself 
claimed 70 percent of her patients were referred by doctors 
barnett was flamboyant often dressing like a showgirl in furs 
and fancy jewels detractors claimed barnett performed abortions 
for the money but others said she performed many abortions for 
free 
during her career she made 9 million but with her resources 
exhausted by high living and legal fees she died at age 77 with 
less than 15000 
only when she was dying of cancer in the oregon womens 
correctional center did she agree not to perform another abortion 
