<TEXT>
from prisons and reeducation camps in vietnam 
nguyen chi thien wrote of despair of loved ones and of dreams of 
freedom 
through poetry he found a way to let his thoughts escape from 
the swamplands where he spent nearly half his life 
human rights groups have conflicting reports on thiens fate 
with some sources saying he died in jail and others suggesting he 
remains imprisoned his plight has drawn attention of writers 
around the world and now his works are part of an effort to 
highlight the risks writers take to express themselves 
on wednesday a us chapter of the pen organization a leading 
voice of international literary freedom will honor thien with one 
of two freedomtowrite awards 
