<TEXT>
in his first 100 days president bush put the 
imperial trappings of the white house in storage the place now 
rings with the squeal of grandchildren and the clang of horseshoes 
born to wealth and privilege george herbert walker bush brought 
to the executive mansion the downtoearth tastes and attitudes of 
a common person hot dogs and baseball games barbecues and country 
music guided tours of the grounds side trips to tourist 
attractions 
yet for all the bustle of the white house these days the 
nations 41st president often rides about town in a silent 
motorcade politely stopping at red lights to avoid tying up 
traffic 
historians and political analysts may differ over the 
presidents accomplishments in these first 100 days but few will 
deny hes been enjoying every one of them 
bush is sort of a james stewart figure said rep newt 
gingrich of georgia the house republican whip recalling the mix 
of awshucks naivete and stubbornness in the actors 
characterization in the movie classic mr smith goes to 
washington 
the presidents personal style is nice and warm and collegial 
its just the way he is hes also a very tough man gingrich 
said adding reagan was a star bush is more of a senior 
playercoach type 
riding the crest of 60 percentplus approval ratings in public 
opinion polls bush is settling with obvious relish and comfort 
into the job that he long coveted at the same time he has 
eschewed efforts to compare him with his predecessor who also 
scored high in the polls 
i certainly know something about following a class act bush 
told a recent audience 
bush himself can joke that his first 100 days are about the 
same as martin van burens who was forced in his first 100 days 
to deal with one of the nations worst financial panics and the 
long depression that followed and whose name the president enjoys 
invoking 
but bushs constantmotion style gives aides and reporters a 
difficult time keeping up with him 
beginning work each day at 7 am bush routinely puts in 
11hour workdays in the oval office although he also has been 
known to slip away in the middle of the afternoon to play tennis 
jog throw horseshoes or play racquetball in a congressional 
gymnasium 
while he seldom held news conferences during his presidential 
campaign bush has met roughly once a week with reporters since 
taking office in forums ranging from regular news conferences to 
smallgroup chats in the oval office 
hes travelled to four foreign counties and 17 states in his 
first three months in office 
bush set a populist tone on his first full day in office 
opening the white house and its grounds to the public and hes had 
a stream of visitors in ever since among them democratic leaders 
who got little such attention from reagan 
ive been here more since bush has been president than i 
was in eight years under his predecessor said rep jack brooks 
dtexas 
congressional leaders who have met frequently with bush say he 
is a good listener at highlevel meetings but a tough negotiator 
i am amazed at how much at peace with himself he is and 
really knows where he wants to go how he wants to do it said 
his chief of staff john sununu 
sununu said bush has no trouble making quick decisions even 
though the president himself jokes that people say im 
indecisive i dont know about that 
aides and associates say he gives careful attention to detail 
even checking travel manifests to make sure there arent too many 
staff members on trips while always keeping up to speed on the 
issues of the day 
in addition to daily intelligence and national security 
briefings he reads about five papers as far as i can see each 
morning said his wife barbara 
participants at cabinet meetings say the president often stays 
on the sidelines and lets others do most of the talking while 
other times jumping in and vigorously leading the discussions 
he enjoys the give and take said vice president dan quayle 
he enjoys having ideas put forward he enjoys the competition 
of ideas and discussion of policy and where we ought to be going 
bush who as vice president had lunch once a week with reagan 
has carried the custom forward he eats a private lunch each 
thursday with quayle who said he has complete access to bush and 
can go into his office any time he wants 
bush is a much more open gregarious outgoing president than 
weve had in a long time said norman ornstein a political 
analyst with the american enterprise institute 
his early reputation is that this is a president who makes 
things happen once you establish that reputation you are going to 
carry it to your advantage for a long time 
still others have trouble focusing on bushs true political and 
policy identity in all the swirl of activity 
the nonimage is the image he has created for himself said 
tom griscom who was reagans communications director 
bush after all is the president who begins speeches on 
education with the phrase you know who talks about things 
and stuff who frequently stumbles over his own lines 
its been said that sometimes i dont speak in very good 
