at a tavern in coburg theres pickled 
spotted owl egg and fried or broasted spotted owl on the menu 
an oakridge tavern held a spotted owl dinner two weeks ago and 
attracted a big crowd 
a springfield man plans to market spotted owl jerky 
the food isnt really owl meat but the spoofs are signs of how 
high emotions are running in oregons timber country over the 
northern spotted owl and its habitat in oldgrowth forest coveted 
by loggers 
bill allison publisher of high lead magazine in eugene said 
hes sold more than 600 tshirts that feature a hairy logger 
carrying an owl on a tray with the caption save a logger eat an 
owl 
despite the protestations the us fish and wildlife service 
said today in washington dc it will tell a federal court in 
seattle next week that protection of the spotted owl as a 
threatened species is warranted 
listing a species as threatened is slightly less restrictive 
than listing a species as endangered said george leonard 
associate chief of the us forest service however it still could 
lock loggers out of much of the oldgrowth forest west of the 
cascade range in oregon and washington 
the fish and wildlife service earlier decided against listing 
the owl as endangered but a reassessment was ordered by us 
district judge thomas zilly in seattle zilly found the earlier 
decision was not supported by evidence compiled by fish and 
wildlife 
under the endangered species act a species is considered 
endangered if it is in danger of extinction throughout all or a 
significant part of its range a species is considered threatened 
if it is likely to become an endangered species in the 
foreseeable future throughout all or a significant portion of its 
range 
rolla anderson who works at the bohemia inc plywood plant in 
vaughn has written a poem about the owl in it he tells of a man 
seeing a spotted owl contentedly sitting on a limb in a stand of 
oldgrowth trees 
even tho i soon may lose my job 
and stand to lose my home 
i cant explain the peace i felt 
like none ive never known 
standing there in that quiet place 
far from the sound of cars 
i looked around took careful aim 
then blew his brains to mars 
environmentalists who say the owl is faced with extinction 
because of logging and timber industry representatives who say the 
trees are needed to keep the industry alive in the northwest agree 
that the spotted owl dinners tshirts and poems are signs of 
frustration and fear 
