they find it convenient to turn their workers heads around 
and say look its that owl thats taking your job when theyre 
sending logs overseas she said 
its just a fear thing and i hope workers can look beyond the 
fear to see whats happenning 
allison said hes received only one complaint about his 
tshirts that came from a timber industry official who said the 
shirts are inappropriate and thought it would be better to show an 
owl or other wildlife living in harmony with good forest practices 
allison accuses both sides of tunnel vision 
the spotted owl is a means to an end he said if it 
wasnt that it would be the pigtailed titmouse the 
environmentalists goal is to save old growth 
as for the timber industry he said how can people like 
weyerhaeuser send logs to japan then go bid on federal timber 
thats not fair 
anderson said he really doesnt advocate shooting spotted owls 
but he lost his job in california when redwood national park was 
established 
i just kind of got a new start and id hate to see it go down 
the tubes here he said 
im not so dumb that i think the owl is the only problem he 
said theyre shipping logs overseas i realize that there 
might be a poem coming on that one of these days 
the owl gets focused on he said because its kind of a 
symbol 
