walls onto cars parked on the street 23 floors below 
three hours later sheila and don walters of westport conn 
who had been staying in the maria isabel sheraton said they 
decided to continue their vacation and go on to acapulco 
im still actually dizzy from it mrs walters said i 
dont feel i have my legs under me yet 
she remembered sitting in their sixthfloor room waking up with 
a cup of coffee just before the quake 
there was a do not disturb sign on the inside of the door 
wiggling i was sitting there trying to wake up wondering what 
was making the sign move about five minutes later the whole 
building began shaking 
i felt like i was going to pass out i was really frightened 
it was a sort of panic attack she said 
but her husband everyone agreed stayed calm throughout 
it was like being on the top of a flagpole he said 
richard cummings of selden ny recovering from a twoday bout 
of illness tried to get out of bed when he heard the bathroom door 
bang and felt the building sway 
it was strong enough to make me fall back down on my bed when 
i got up he said thats when i realized what was happening 
lauren wilson of henleyonthames england had been in an 
earthquake in japan but said it was not as bad as this 
she called her husband phil from the bathroom of their 
15thfloor room 
we sat on the bed and held each other she said 
we could just see our building moving relative to the other 
buildings he said while it seemed like a lot it looked like 
about a foot he said 
