extraordinary personal help from him in their dealings with the 
federal government 
but gingrich during a stormy news conference which his wife 
left in anger acknowledged that some of the investors had a direct 
interest in legislation and that he had handled routine requests 
from some of them 
while house rules prohibit members from accepting gifts worth 
more than 100 from people with direct interest in legislation 
gingrich said the partnership did not violate house rules because 
the 5000 that each investor put into the deal did not constitute 
