<TEXT>
a weekly published what was believed to 
be the first detailed report on the late cardinal josef mindszenty 
and his show trial for treason incarceration and seclusion in the 
us diplomatic mission 
in its latest issue idea carried a frontpage photo showing the 
cardinal praying in front of an altar 
idea was formerly the publication of the hungarian communist 
youth league which is now defunct it now refers to itself as a 
political weekly 
displaying a degree of press freedom unthinkable only months 
ago idea carried an eightpage report that included an account of 
mindszentys trial 
it also made frequent references to his memoirs and printed a 
speech hungarys roman catholic prelate made on nov 3 1956 a day 
before soviet tanks quashed a popular uprising against soviet rule 
in the speech the cardinal said the main aim of the hungarians 
should be the revitalization of the nation and demanded an 
allout effort of the entire country for progress 
mindszenty also said hungarys fate will be decided by what 
the russian empire decides to do we didnt attack russia and we 
hope that russian troops will be withdrawn from hungary 
however it took almost 33 years for the soviets to begin a 
withdrawal a first batch of soviet tanks were pulled out tuesday 
starting a partial pullout of 10000 red army soldiers 
mindszenty was arrested in 1948 as an enemy of communism and 
following a humiliating trial was sentenced to life in prison on 
trumpedup charges of high treason 
in 1956 he was freed from prison by hungarian revolutionaries 
after the soviets crushed the uprising mindszenty found shelter in 
the us mission in budapest until 1971 when he left under an 
agreement worked out between the vatican and hungary 
after a short stay in rome mindszenty settled in vienna where 
he died in 1975 at age 83 
konrad szanto a franciscan and historian was quoted by the 
magazine as saying there were increasing signs of a broad demand 
for the rehabilitation of mindszenty along with others who were 
imprisoned on similar phony charges 
last month imre pozsgay a politburo member and leading party 
reformer said mindszentys trial would be reviewed as part of the 
reexamination of all political trials in hungary between 1945 and 
1962 
