a key figure in two 
federal investigations involving washington mayor marion barry was 
convicted tuesday of drug trafficking stemming from an undercover 
fbi operation 
an eightwoman fourman jury deliberated for 90 minutes before 
finding former virgin islands government consultant charles lewis 
guilty of all four drug counts against him the us district court 
trial took two days 
lewis 48 was charged with two counts of drug possession and 
two counts of distribution in the sale of 550 worth of crack a 
cocaine derivative to undercover fbi agents last month 
us attorney richard harris said each count carries a maximum 
sentence of 20 years and 1 million 
chief us district court judge david v obrien set sentencing 
for june 14 and released lewis on unsecured bond of 10000 lewis 
left the courtroom accompanied by his brother and sister 
lewis had pleaded innocent but did not testify 
lewis faces 10 felony charges in washington in a separate case 
in which district of columbia police reportedly were called off an 
attempted drug buy from lewis while barry was visiting his hotel 
room in the city 
a federal grand jury is looking into the circumstances of 
barrys visit to the hotel 
