kelly mcgillis seems so strongwilled and 
controlled both on the screen and off that you wonder if she ever 
had doubts in her waitress days that she would reach the top of the 
acting world 
oh yeah all the time she admits but theres also that 
part of you the driven side that says i will and has that 
kind of confidence but i think you will always have selfdoubt i 
still do i continually wonder if i would ever work again maybe 
thats one of the things that drives me 
contributing to her air of confidence is her appearance stately 
if not quite regal with a cool beauty that would have melted the 
late alfred hitchcock was her height ever a drawback 
not to me maybe to other people but no i dont think so i 
suppose people say how come you always play sort of stronger 
women not the vulnerable victim types i can maybe attribute 
that to my height its sort of hard to be a victim when youre 
5feet10 and youre bigger than a lot of guys youre working 
with 
significantly jodie foster was the gangrape victim in the 
accused and mcgillis was the prosecutor who sought justice for 
her in her new film winter people mcgillis plays both victim 
and protagonist she is an unwed mother ostrasized by her family 
who stirs up a smoldering mountain feud and then resolves it with 
an act of supreme sacrifice 
the columbia release was filmed in the locale of the john ehle 
novel the blue ridge mountains under conditions that duplicated 
the hardships of living on the land 50 years ago 
it was pretty rough to be out in the elements for so many 
hours a day she recalled it was cold and wet and damp 
the emotional challenges of playing coley wright were very 
demanding but thats why i did it i wanted to see if i could hit 
those emotional peaks and valleys 
coley is a bit rebellious but at the same time she is very 
traditional she is very strong and impetuous but at the same time 
very weak and feminine which are all sort of interesting things to 
portray in a character because thats how we are in real life 
any resemblance between coley and kelly 
mmmm yeah i think so she said i think that im a bit 
rebellious and yet very traditional at the same time and i think 
im strong and weak at the same time im very singleminded when i 
get an idea nothing can stand in my way or change my mind 
filmmakers have discovered that about kelly mcgillis while she 
doesnt push her weight around on a set she does like to 
contribute to the creative process and why not 
i must say ive been very fortunate in not working with that 
type of dictatorial director ive always felt that i could at 
least bring up an idea and they can say thats not a good idea 
or i dont like that i dont take that personally 
ive never worked with the kind of person who said just shut 
up and do it this way if i did i probably would rebel a lot 
she said 
after a certain amount of time an actor or an actress knows 
their character better than anyone else around once youve 
assimilated and really become this person you know what you would 
do in a given situation than anyone else on that set 
mcgillis 31 spent her early years in thousand oaks halfway 
between los angeles and ventura by a weird coincidence her father 
was physician for her winter people costar kurt russell then 
a disney child star 
i had a big crush on him when i was 8 years old she said 
the mcgillis family moved to newport beach in orange county 
we went on vacation and never came back 
when i was in high school i took theater said mcgillis 
whose new hair style is closecropped blond and brown i dropped 
out of high school to pursue acting which didnt make my family 
happy i studied a few years at the pacific conservatory of the 
performing arts then i was accepted to julliard in new york where 
i studied for four years 
during her last year at the julliard school she auditioned for 
a role with tom conti in reuben reuben she appeared in a few 
tv movies without much notice then director peter weir saw her in 
reuben reuben and wanted her to test for the amish woman 
opposite harrison ford in witness 
i said of course i know all about the amish but i really 
didnt she said so i had to spend the weekend in the library 
i had just gotten a job as a waitress in a restaurant where i 
had wanted to work for a long long time when they finally offered 
me witness a week later i felt so bad about quitting the other 
job you always want to work in a new york restaurant where there 
is minimal work and a lot of money 
even after the film she applied for another waitress job because 
she was worried shed never work again witness and top gun 
eased her insecurity 
now she can even take a few months off as she and her boat 
broker husband fred tillman recently did ferrying a yacht from 
the east coast to san diego 
