the highprofile italian retailer benetton 
has opened its first store in poland shocking shoppers accustomed 
to empty shelves with mounds of colorful clothing and prices in 
their own currency 
sales clerks reported the most common question was dollars or 
zlotys as a storefront on warsaws main shopping street ulica 
marszalkowska on monday turned into a glistening benetton outlet 
with its crisp modern look 
the italian retailer is on the leading edge of marketing by 
western companies in the east bloc poland has been trying to 
attract such businesses to help shore up its ailing economy 
stacks and stacks of knitwear in bright hues of orange blue 
and yellow were folded on open shelves in the warsaw store on 
monday a bevy of saleswomen in benetton outfits volunteered 
assistance 
